One cleric with infinite mana COULD keep the MT up in this fight, assuming he times heals perfectly, never gets hit with the AE and the mob stays slowed. I would strongly advise against that though LOL. I'd recommend 3-4 clerics minimum just to keep it safe, or 2-3 clerics and a ton of mod rods. This beast is a pretty long fight, but really not that difficult.<br>
<br>
Rhag1: Easy fight, 2-3 clerics. We killed him with 3 groups but could easily have done it with 2.<br>
<br>
Rhag2: Celest or Remove Curse both deal pretty easily with the DoT, just make sure someone stays on top of it. The damn monk that forgot to tell me he was cursed kinda ticked me off wasting my mana with heals when I could have cured him. I noticed the curse on the caster more quickly since they shouldn't be taking any damage.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzxing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zxing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 4:21:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9657.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rhag's and Thought Horror Overfiend!</span><hr size=1> Yes, people that don't ask for cures right away, if they get cursed, deserve to die from it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
We've done rhag 1 with around 20 people, and two clerics. This was back in the first couple days of luclin release, so we had no idea what this mob was about, especially how his agro worked. So both our clerics bit it early on, and we had to kill him with druids and shamans healing.<br>
<br>
It becomes a fun fight when you have no clerics to CH you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
So yes, I think he can easily be done with around 10 people in NToV gear. We had very little in the way of primal then.<br>
<br>
EDIT: To give you an idea of the THO fight, I did 34,794 damage to him in a combo of switching back and forth between primal 2h and swiftblade/priceless after avatar proc. So he either has many, many more hp then people think, or a combination of insane ac and insane regen. He does have really high ac, so I'm guessing that's what it is. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzxing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zxing</A> at: 2/10/02 4:27:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uprodigious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prodigious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 7:15:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9657.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rhag's and Thought Horror Overfiend!</span><hr size=1> THO used to have like no regen, was that changed? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhuneyy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>huneyy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 6:37:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9657.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rhag's and Thought Horror Overfiend!</span><hr size=1> just curious, ive heard rumors of THO having an AE fear now as well...can anyone that has took him on recently confirm this plz <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   thx ! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/